title: Plane stuck on runway at OR Tambo International Airport
text:
Johannesburg - An aircraft came to a standstill on one of the runways at OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg on Monday, Airports Company SA (Acsa) said.
- Are you there? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos .
An anonymous caller told News24 that it was a British Airways Boeing 737 and its main wheel had collapsed.
Acsa spokesperson Colin Naidoo told News24 the aircraft was causing a slight delay of about 15 minutes.
